          <td width="25" align="center" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="365" align="left" valign="middle"><div align="justify">
		  <font class="textHelp">
		  	The display shows all power outlets that you are allowed to access and manage. 
			<br>The lamp icons indicate the current status of the power outlet. Clicking the 
			lamp icon toggles the state of the outlet.
			<br>Click the "Cycle" button of any outlet which is ON to momentarily power it 
			off. 
			<br>Click the lock icon to lock/unlock the outlet; Locking the outlet prevents 
			accidental changes to the state of the power outlet.
			<br>Clicking on "Save Outlets State" saves the current configuration to the flash 
			memory of <%getLabel("powername");%>.
			<br>To assign a name to the outlet or to change the power up interval, click on 
			the "Edit" button.
		  </font></div></td>
